dataList.title: La Manchaland
dataList.content: Ahh...

dataList.title: La Manchaland
dataList.content: I have sinned. I have sinned once again today, I confess...

dataList.title: La Manchaland
dataList.content: Take... take me to the Priest... They said it's all going to be okay if I visit the Priest when I feel the thirst... They said...
So that Priest is... in there, right?

dataList.title: La Manchaland
dataList.content: You're going to have to wait your turn... the other... ones sought the Priest too... Must've been sinners as well...

dataList.title: La Manchaland
dataList.content: So... there might be a... queue...

dataList.title: La Manchaland
dataList.content: Oh, the Priest... gladly... ...ing the sins in our stead...
<We should probably... check what's behind this door, right?>
I shall take the vanguard, Manager Esquire!
<Woah...>
Villains! I—
<color=#ffef23>What I am certain of, is that this intruder will never leave us alone until we open our gates.</color>
<color=#ffef23>We must put an end to this insolency soon, wouldn't you agree?</color>
<color=#cc2424>I suppose you will understand me when you create your own ■■■■■■■...</color>
<color=#cc2424>Worry not. I intend to put an end to this today. I have been planning to do so for a while.</color>
When we entered, we saw... a dying Bloodfiend, nearing his death.
His mask was already cloven in half, revealing the pitiful tragedy behind.
It no longer served as a mask to hide his face.
Have you... come here... to confess your sins?
Ah... what joy... Rarely do I receive those who... are so willing to confess...
This one... He's only a smoldering stub.
I could snuff out his embers with a gentle stomp.
